    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc.00020.002.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place"><handShift rend="printed"/>The Pilot Editorial Roo[ms,]<ptr target="med.00659_n1"/></name>
                    <name type="place"><handShift rend="manuscript"/>[Boston,]</name>
                    <date when="1881-09-21"><choice>
                            <abbr>Se[pt.]</abbr>
                            <expan>September</expan>
                        </choice> 21</date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>Dear Mr. Whitma[n:]</salute>
            </opener>

            <p>Can [you] come, with Bartlett, Kate, and [a c]harming lady and myself, [to see] Mr. Quincy
                Shaw's pic[tures], on Friday at 2 p.m.[?] I shall call for you [wi]th carriage. [Don't]
                say no: you'll [enjoy] it. If you don't answer, I [shall] take it for "<hi rend="underline">yes</hi>."</p>

            <closer>
                <signed>Boyle [O'Reil]ly.</signed>
            </closer>
            <postscript>
                <p>Shall see you at Bartletts Thursday evening.</p>
            </postscript>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="loc.00020.001.jpg" type="verso"/>
            <!--The verso of this letter is a manuscript of "The Sobbing of the Bells."-->
        </body>
